%3E%20in%20February%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20what%20I%20intended%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-sues-sam-altman-betrays-openai-mission-chatgpt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20OpenAI%20in%20February%20this%20year%2C%20where%20he%20accused%20the%20company%20of%20violating%20its%20nonprofit%20mission%20by%20partnering%20with%20Microsoft.%20He%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-drops-lawsuit-against-sam-altman-and-openai-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithdrew%20his%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20Musk%20also%20has%20some%20reservations%20about%20how%20open%20AI%20models%20should%20be.%20In%20private%20correspondence%2C%20the%20Tesla%20and%20xAI%20chief%20appeared%20to%20agree%20with%20OpenAI's%20then-chief%20scientist%2C%20Ilya%20Sutskever%2C%20that%20there%20should%20be%20limits%20to%20openness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20get%20closer%20to%20building%20AI%2C%20it%20will%20make%20sense%20to%20start%20being%20less%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20Sutskever%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Findex%2Fopenai-elon-musk%2F%23email-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemail%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Musk%20in%20January%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Open%20in%20OpenAI%20means%20that%20everyone%20should%20benefit%20from%20the%20fruits%20of%20AI%20after%20its%20built%2C%20but%20it's%20totally%20OK%20to%20not%20share%20the%20science%20(even%20though%20sharing%20everything%20is%20definitely%20the%20right%20strategy%20in%20the%20short%20and%20possibly%20medium%20term%20for%20recruitment%20purposes)%2C%26quot%3B%20Sutskever%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYup%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Altman%20and%20Musk%20didn't%20immediately%20respond