0reminded%20of%20the%20night%20before%20Southwest%20made%20its%20announcement%2C%20when%20I%20flew%20with%20the%20airline%20from%20Burbank%2C%20California%2C%20to%20Denver%2C%20and%20found%20the%20boarding%20and%20seating%20process%20as%20easy%2C%20straightforward%2C%20and%20pleasant%20as%20I%20always%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b1f51d82-152a-415e-9ee1-460339871a6d%5C%22%3EAvoiding%20the%20dreaded%20'gate%20lice'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProbably%20my%20favorite%20thing%20about%20flying%20Southwest%20is%20lining%20up%20to%20board.%20Because%20of%20the%20assigned%20boarding%20number%2C%20I%20know%20in%20advance%20exactly%20when%20I'm%20going%20to%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20almost%20always%20fly%20with%20just%20a%20carry-on%20and%20no%20checked%20luggage%20%E2%80%94%20in%20part%20because%20I'm%20worried%20about%20my%20bag%20getting%20lost.%20When%20I%20fly%20on%20other%20airlines%2C%20I%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20trying%20to%20get%20on%20the%20plane%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%20so%20they%20don't%20run%20out%20of%20overhead%20space%20and%20force%20me%20to%20gate-check%20my%20bag.%20I%20also%20just%20like%20to%20ensure%20that%20I%20can%20actually%20store%20my%20bag%20above%20where%20I'm%20sitting%20and%20not%20in%20whatever%20overhead%20space%20happens%20to%20be%20left%20by%20the%20time%20I%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20typically%20means%20rushing%20to%20the%20gate%20to%20try%20and%20stake%20out%20a%20good%20spot%20so%20I%20can%20board%20as%20early%20as%20possible%20in%20my%20designated%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20means%20navigating%20the%20chaos%20that%20can%20be%20found%20at%20essentially%20every%20other%20airline's%20gate%20besides%20Southwest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20other%20airlines%20technically%20have%20boarding%20groups%20that%20are%20intended%20to%20create%20order.%20But%20inevitably%2C%20people%20in%20groups%20four%20and%20five%20are%20standing%20around%2C%20clogging%20up%20the%20area%2C%20even%20though%20only%20groups%20one%20and%20two%20are%20boarding%20%E2%80%94%20forcing%20you%20to%20awkwardly%20scoot%20through%20the%20crowd%2C%20asking%20people%20what%20boarding%20group%20they%20are%20in%20just%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20actually%20get%20in%20with%20your%20designated%20group%20and%20aren't%20left%20in%20the%20dust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20don't%20call%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-pet-peeves-passengers-gate-lice-boarding-crowds-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bgate%20lice%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20with%20many%20airlines%20I%20could%20simply%20pay%20for%20an%20early%20boarding%20position%20(often%20in%20addition%20to%20paying%20for%20the%20seat%20assignment%20itself)%2C%20but%20with%20Southwest%2C%20all%20I%20had%20to%20do%20was%20make%20sure%20I%20pulled%20out%20my%20phone%20and%20checked%20in%20exactly%2024%20hours%20before%20my%20flight%20to%20get%20a%20decent%20enough%20boarding%20position.%20I%20always%20felt%20like%20I%20never%20had%20to%20plan%20ahead%20to%20get%20a%20good%20seat%20on%20a%20Southwest%20flight%20%E2%80%94%20I%20just%20had%20to%20check%20in%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20with%20Southwest%2C%20I%20could%20also%20pay%20in%20advance%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Ftravel%2Fairline-news%2F2024%2F06%2F03%2Fsouthwest-airlines-early-boarding-perk-fees%2F73957539007%2F%23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEarlyBird%20check-in%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20costs%20between%20%2415%20to%20%2499.%20And%2C%20if%20for%20some%20reason%20I%20was%20late%20to%20check%20in%20and%20got%20a%20late%20boarding%20number%2C%20I%20could%20still%20pay%20for%20an%20earlier%20boarding%20position%20after%20the%20fact%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20can%20now%20cost%20anywhere%20from%20%2430%20to%20%24149%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20absolutely%20need%20to%20board%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECudahy%20noted%20that%20Southwest%20said%20it's%20gotten%20a%20lot%20of%20positive%20feedback%20from%20customers%20on%20how%20calm%20and%20orderly%20their%20boarding%20process%20is%20and%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bwant%20to%20try%20and%20keep%20the%20general%20spirit%20of%20that%20as%20they%20adapt%20it%20to%20fit%20the%20assigned%20seating%20model.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it's%20unclear%20at%20this%20point%20what%20that%20would%20look%20like%20with%20seat%20assignments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Passengers%20%20boarding%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a303ad1a227600e631d6c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESouthwest%20was%20unique%20for%20having%20customers%20simply%20choose%20their%20seat%20as%20they%20boarded%20the%20plane.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227cb138cb-aa6f-4e12-b90f-ee11286a292a%5C%22%3EFast%20and%20easy%20boarding%20process%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECalmness%20wasn't%20the%20only%20thing%20Southwest's%20strategy%20had%20going%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20the%20fastest%20in%20the%20industry%20forever%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20boarding%20process%20that%20they%20used%2C%26quot%3B%20Jason%20Steffen%2C%20an%20astrophysicist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nevada%2C%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20who%20came%20up%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fairlines%2Funited-airlines-boarding-planes-window-seats-wilma-fd7d9394%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplane-boarding%20method%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20says%20is%20faster%20than%20any%20used%20by%20the%20airlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteffen's%20boarding%20process%20was%20even%20tested%20against%20Southwest's%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DLzmL-GiE3QE%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPBS's%20%26quot%3BMaking%20Stuff%20Faster%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20a%20decade%20ago.%20(Spoiler%20alert%3A%20Steffen's%20process%20won%2C%20but%20the%20Southwest%20representative%20on%20the%20show%20said%20he%20did%20not%20think%20it%20was%20practical%20enough%20in%20real-world%20situations.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20my%20own%20Southwest%20flight%20Wednesday%20night%20reminded%20me%2C%20the%20open%20boarding%20method%20is%20fast%20%E2%80%94%20in%20part%20because%20people%20naturally%20spread%20out%20as%20they%20try%20to%20pick%20window%20and%20aisle%20seats%20up%20and%20down%20the%20plane%20before%20filling%20in%20the%20middles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20happened%20to%20get%20particularly%20lucky%20on%20my%20flight.%20My%20partner%20and%20I%20boarded%20at%20the%20end%20of%20group%20A%20and%20grabbed%20an%20aisle%20and%20window%20seat%20in%20an%20empty%20row%2C%20of%20course%20with%20the%20hope%20that%20no%20one%20would%20sit%20in%20the%20middle.%20The%20plane%20wasn't%20full%2C%20and%20we%20ended%20up%20having%20the%20row%20to%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20on%20full%20flights%2C%20as%20long%20as%20we%20check%20in%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20we%20almost%20always%20sit%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20families%20also%20love%20Southwest's%20open%20seating%20policy%20for%20this%20reason.%20Similar%20to%20other%20airlines%2C%20Southwest%20allows%20families%20with%20children%20under%20seven%20to%20board%20early%2C%20between%20A%20and%20B%20groups%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20generally%20find%20seats%20together.%20For%20some%20people%2C%20they%20find%20it%20easier%20than%20picking%20seats%20for%20everyone%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2214167fef-d974-4f5b-97b6-4cae9e3b4d4c%5C%22%3EPart%20of%20the%20Southwest%20brand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20many%20customers%20may%20ultimately%20welcome%20the%20change%2C%20the%20open%20seating%20has%20been%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20Southwest%20brand%20for%20over%20half%20a%20century%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20its%20two%20free%20check%20bags%20(which%20the%20airline%20says%20isn't%20going%20away)%20and%20low-cost%20fare%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20mistake%20a%20Southwest%20gate%20when%20you%20walk%20up%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Cudahey%20said%20of%20the%20airline's%20pillars%20that%20mark%20the%20boarding%20numbers%20for%20passengers%20to%20line%20up%20next%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20Southwest%20will%20find%20a%20way%20to%20maintain%20a%20boarding%20system%20that%20still%20uses%20those%20pillars%2C%20and%20that%20still%20maintains%20the%20calmness%20at%20their%20gates%20that%20always%20greets%20me%20like%20a%20warm%20hug%20in%20an%20otherwise%20chaotic%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20without%20the%20open%20seating%2C%20the%20airline%20is%20losing%20part%20of%20what%20sets%20it%20apart%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20that%20means%20gaining%20new%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20kind%20of%20comes%20down%20to%20is%20their%20cult%20following%20getting%20in%20the%20way%20of%20a%20broader%20appeal%3F%26quot%3B%20Steffen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-will-miss-southwest-airlines-unassigned-seating-policy-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721963597000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a304adaab37011780ab8c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-will-miss-southwest-airlines-unassigned-seating-policy-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Southwest%20Airlines%20said%20it%20was%20doing%20away%20with%20its%20open%20seating%20policy%20because%20customers%20don't%20like%20it.%20But%20here's%20why%20I%20loved%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40businessinsider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A314%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-will-miss-southwest-airlines-unassigned-seating-policy-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A