0height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChina%20announced%20on%20Sunday%20that%20it's%20planning%20to%20raise%20its%20retirement%20age.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20say%20it's%20a%20move%20that's%20been%20needed%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20despite%20fierce%20backlash%20online.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20China%2C%20some%20women%20get%20to%20retire%20at%2050%20%E2%80%94%20even%20when%20their%20life%20expectancy%20is%20over%2080%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBuried%20under%20scores%20of%20paragraphs%2C%20a%20single%20line%20in%20a%20new%20document%20from%20Beijing%20has%20shaken%20China's%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20leaders%2C%20who%20convened%20last%20week%20to%20discuss%20their%20economy's%20direction%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.cn%2Fzhengce%2F202407%2Fcontent_6963770.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealed%20dozens%20of%20resolutions%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Sunday%20%E2%80%94%20including%20their%20desire%20to%20raise%20the%20standard%20retirement%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20specifics%20were%20given%2C%20and%20the%20resolution%20said%20any%20changes%20would%20emphasize%20being%20%26quot%3Bvoluntary%20and%20flexible.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20the%20signs%20are%20clear%3A%20Beijing%20is%20finally%20ready%20to%20shift%20a%20rule%20that's%20governed%20lives%20for%20over%20six%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-wants-raise-retirement-age-people-not-happy-retire-60-2024-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520party%2520plans%2520to%2520raise%2CChinese%2520social%2520media%2520site%2520Weibo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeeply%20unpopular%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20it%20has%20been%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Ffrance-protests-retirement-age-macron-strikes-1abb098b104f2b7094e51e650218771d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20workers%20protested%20a%20similar%20verdict%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20China%20have%20taken%20the%20statement%20as%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20end%20for%20a%20monolith%20of%20working%20life%20as%20they've%20known%20it%20since%20the%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20Thursday%2C%20the%20hashtag%20%26quot%3Bretiring%20late%26quot%3B%20has%20surged%20to%20130%20million%20views%20on%20Xiaohongshu%2C%20China's%20version%20of%20Instagram.%20People%20took%20their%20complaints%20this%20week%20to%20Weibo%2C%20China's%20version%20of%20X%2C%20in%20similar%20threads%2C%20which%20were%20later%20censored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20experts%20and%20think%20tanks%20have%20long%20said%20this%20is%20a%20policy%20change%20that%20an%20aging%20China%20desperately%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9f85057-4406-46ab-bf84-cb4c35c75535%5C%22%3EChina's%20low%20retirement%20age%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20with%20blue-collar%20jobs%20in%20China%20can%20retire%20and%20collect%20pension%20checks%20as%20early%20as%2050%2C%20and%20those%20in%20offices%20can%20leave%20the%20workforce%20at%2055.%20Even%20the%20retirement%20age%20of%2060%20for%20Chinese%20men%20is%20below%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd-ilibrary.org%2Fsites%2Fca401ebd-en%2F1%2F3%2F3%2F6%2Findex.html%3FitemId%3D%2Fcontent%2Fpublication%2Fca401ebd-en%26_csp_%3D9d37797bd84847326841f27f588be463%26itemIGO%3Doecd%26itemContentType%3Dbook%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dlinklink%2520copied!-%2CNormal%2520retirement%2520age%2Cyears%2520(hence%2520around%25202064).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20average%20of%20about%2064.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20the%20standard%20set%20in%201951%2C%20but%20it's%20outdated%20because%20if%20we%20look%20back%2C%20the%20life%20expectancy%20at%20birth%20was%2043%20in%201950%20and%20then%2048%20in%201958%2C%26quot%3B%20Sabrina%20Luk%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20social%20sciences%20at%20the%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University%20in%20Singapore%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20life%20expectancy%20has%20now%20soared%20to%2075.4%20years%20for%20men%20and%2080.8%20years%20for%20women%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stats.gov.cn%2Fsj%2Fndsj%2F2023%2Findexeh.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficial%20government%20statistics.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20change%20was%20probably%2020%20years%20overdue%2C%26quot%3B%20Shaun%20Rein%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Shanghai-based%20China%20Market%20Research%20Group%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20ridiculous%20that%20people%20would%20graduate%20from%20college%20or%20from%20a%20vocational%20school%20at%20age%2022%2C%20work%20for%2028%20years%2C%20and%20then%20be%20retired%20for%20another%2030%20to%2040%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuk%2C%20who%20researches%20aging%20in%20Asia%2C%20said%20Beijing%20could%20look%20at%20creating%20a%20national%20standard%20in%20retirement%20ages%20across%20genders.%20It's%20currently%20running%20a%20lopsided%20policy%20of%20letting%20women%20retire%20up%20to%2010%20years%20earlier%20despite%20them%20living%20significantly%20longer%20on%20average%20than%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20almost%20every%20country%2C%20women%20outlive%20men%20by%20about%20four%20years%20on%20average%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20China%2C%20the%20women%20live%20more%20than%20five%20years%20longer%20than%20men.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20think%20tanks%2C%20including%20the%20state-run%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcisscass.com%2Ffazhanbginfo.aspx%3Fids%3D23%26fl%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20forecast%20that%20the%20country%20will%20aim%20for%20all%20workers%20to%20retire%20at%2065.%20There%20is%20no%20official%20word%20yet%20on%20the%20new%20retirement%20ages%20or%20whether